criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

        Patients must elicit 3 of the 6 symptoms to be included:

          -  forty five years of age and over.

          -  stiffness for less than thirty minutes;

          -  crepitus;

          -  bony tenderness;

          -  bony enlargement;

          -  no palpable joint warmth.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  previous lower limb joint injection within three months;

          -  previous hip or knee joint replacement;

          -  any severe cognitive, cardio- respiratory, musculoskeletal or neurological - diagnosis
             that prevents participants from exercising;

          -  insoles or braces;

          -  ligament instability;

          -  participants with a body mass index (BMI) over 40 will be issued with a choice of
             completing in the study or being managed by the National Health Service weight
             management service;

          -  other minor health related issues will be assessed prior to the commencement of the
             study to ensure safe practice.
